  "articleSummary": "The article argues that PostgreSQL teams should master all three native search tools—**full-text search** (`tsvector`/`GIN`), **trigrams** (`pg_trgm`), and **exact-match indexes**—to avoid overcomplicating search logic and unnecessary reliance on external services. It frames search as a matter of *matching the tool to the query shape*: full-text search for semantic content, trigrams for fuzzy/typo-tolerant matching, and exact indexes for binary matches. The tone is analytical and tutorial, emphasizing practical guidance over theoretical debate, with recurring metaphors like \"input shape\" and \"query",
